@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@prev "Main"
                                             @{b}Introduction@{ub}

When you've had an Amiga for a while, and you've installed software all over the place, despite your
best efforts, you finish up with AmigaGuide documents and ReadMe files scattered across your hard
drive(s). Now this is fine, until you come to want a specific guide, or aren't sure exactly which
guide you are looking for. Wouldn't it be nice to have all your AmigaGuides and ReadMe's available
from a single hotkey, and to be able to search for keywords throughout them all. That's where GHelp 
comes in.

Quite simply, GHelp consists of two programs that work together as a package.

GHelpGen searches your hard drives (the exact search paths are configurable) and creates an index
which is used by GHelpGUI

GHelp is a small commodity that sits in the background waiting for you to press your (user definable)
hotkey combination.

I know that there are other programs available on AmiNet to do something similar, but those that I've
tried either don't work, or, they don't provide the complete solution that GHelp does.

All I can say is, Try it. If you like it, tell your friends and @{"me" link "Author"}, if you don't, tell @{"me" link "Author"}. 

If you can see a way to improve it,  tell @{"me" link "Author"}, but see the @{"To Do" link "New"} section first to get an idea of where I 
am going with this.

Steve Hargreaves.  
@next "Distribution"
@endnode

